42500683,address_book,joelibaceta/address_book,Agenda personal desarrollado con Ruby on Rails,,Ruby,"Ruby, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, CoffeeScript",0,0,0,0,2015-09-15T06:53:54Z,2015-09-15T06:57:16Z,2015-09-16T08:14:05Z,GNU General Public License v2.0,== README Production site https://agile-caverns-7772.herokuapp.com/ Things you may want to cover: * Ruby version Ruby 2.1.5 Rails 4.2 * System dependencies * Configuration * Database creation rake db:create * Database initialization rake db:migrate rake db:seed * How to run the test suite $ rspec * Deployment instructions $ rake git push heroku,J,Information and communication,high,"The repository is a personal agenda application developed with Ruby on Rails, which serves as a general-purpose tool for managing contacts and schedules. This aligns well with the Information and communication industry as it involves software that facilitates personal organization and communication."
994498344,ALPR-for-Peruvian-License-Plates,joelibaceta/ALPR-for-Peruvian-License-Plates,,,Jupyter Notebook,"Jupyter Notebook, Python, TeX",1,0,1,0,2025-06-02T03:09:51Z,2025-09-15T09:55:13Z,2025-06-06T01:18:48Z,,"# ALPR for Peruvian License Plates 🇵🇪 This repository contains a working application for **Automatic License Plate Recognition (ALPR)** tailored to Peruvian road conditions. The pipeline detects vehicles, locates license plates within them, and extracts their alphanumeric content using OCR. --- ## 🎯 What This Project Does - Detects vehicles in road video footage - Locates license plates (painted or metallic) using a custom YOLOv7-based model - Applies OCR to extract and validate plate numbers <p align=""center""> <img src=""figs/dataset_vehicle_sample.png"" width=""600""/> </p>",H,Transportation and storage,high,"The repository focuses on Automatic License Plate Recognition (ALPR) specifically for vehicles, which is directly applicable to the transportation industry for vehicle monitoring, traffic management, and law enforcement."
