160332493,find-github-friends,joelibaceta/find-github-friends,,,JavaScript,"JavaScript, HTML",0,0,0,0,2018-12-04T09:30:16Z,2018-12-05T00:00:30Z,2018-12-05T00:00:28Z,MIT License,"## Welcome to GitHub Pages You can use the [editor on GitHub](https://github.com/joelibaceta/find-github-friends/edit/master/README.md) to maintain and preview the content for your website in Markdown files. Whenever you commit to this repository, GitHub Pages will run [Jekyll](https://jekyllrb.com/) to rebuild the pages in your site, from the content in your Markdown files. ### Markdown Markdown is a lightweight and easy-to-use syntax for styling your writing. It includes conventions for ```markdown Syntax highlighted code block # Header 1 ## Header 2 ### Header 3 - Bulleted - List 1. Numbered 2. List **Bold** and _Italic_ and `Code` text [Link](url) and ![Image](src) ``` For more details see [GitHub Flavored Markdown](https://guides.github.com/features/mastering-markdown/). ### Jekyll Themes Your Pages site will use the layout and styles from the Jekyll theme you have selected in your [repository settings](https://github.com/joelibaceta/find-github-friends/settings). The name of this",J,Information and communication,high,"The repository appears to be related to GitHub Pages and Markdown, which are tools commonly used in web development and content management, fitting well within the Information and communication industry."
42433904,fix-protocol,joelibaceta/fix-protocol,"FIX message classes, parsing and generation",,Ruby,Ruby,0,7,0,0,2015-09-14T07:30:41Z,2019-09-26T08:33:10Z,2015-01-13T12:08:28Z,MIT License,"FIX Protocol [![Build Status](https://secure.travis-ci.org/Paymium/fix-protocol.png?branch=master)](http://travis-ci.org/Paymium/fix-protocol) [![Coverage Status](https://img.shields.io/coveralls/Paymium/fix-protocol.svg)](https://coveralls.io/r/Paymium/fix-protocol?branch=master) [![Gem Version](https://badge.fury.io/rb/fix-protocol.svg)](http://badge.fury.io/rb/fix-protocol) = This FIX protocol wrapper enables one to easily parse and create messages complying with the FIX 4.4 specification. It includes definitions for admin messages (logon, logout, reject, heartbeat, resend request, test request), for some market data messages (market data request, market data snapshot, and market data incremental refresh) as well as the ability to easily define other ones. ## Message creation example Messages are created by instantiating the relevant message class and serialized using the `#dump` method. ````ruby require 'fix/protocol' msg = FP::Messages::Logon.new msg.sender_comp_id = 'MY_ID' msg.t",K,Financial and insurance activities,high,"The repository focuses on the FIX protocol, which is widely used in financial services for electronic trading and communication between financial institutions. Its functionality is directly applicable to the financial industry."
231591806,gh-contributors,joelibaceta/gh-contributors,Github contributors avatars collage builder,"contributors, github, python3, serverless",Python,Python,4,1,4,2,2020-01-03T13:11:37Z,2022-04-12T15:53:19Z,2020-01-10T23:35:08Z,,"# gh-contributors Github contributors avatars builder ## How to use? Just use it as an image tag `<img src=""https://gh-contributors.now.sh/img?org=facebook&repo=react""/>` <img src=""https://gh-contributors.now.sh/img?org=facebook&repo=react""/> Using size parameter `<img src=""https://gh-contributors.now.sh/img?org=flutter&repo=flutter&size=16""/>` <img src=""https://gh-contributors.now.sh/img?org=flutter&repo=flutter&size=16""/> `<img src=""https://gh-contributors.now.sh/img?org=flutter&repo=flutter&size=40""/>` <img src=""https://gh-contributors.now.sh/img?org=flutter&repo=flutter&size=40""/>",J,Information and communication,high,"The repository is a tool for generating avatars of GitHub contributors, which is primarily used in the context of software development and collaboration on platforms like GitHub. This aligns closely with the Information and communication industry, as it facilitates communication and representation of contributors in digital projects."
