41380782,rails,joelibaceta/rails,Basic Rails App,,Ruby,"Ruby, HTML, CSS, JavaScript",0,0,0,0,2015-08-25T18:29:33Z,2016-05-17T10:04:02Z,2015-02-18T16:18:26Z,,"# Ruby on Rails (4.2.0) ## Using the Pack To use the Pack, we created 2 menu options, which you can find on the right of the menu. These menus can be configured in the `.codio` file. 1. **Start Rails Server** : When you come into your Project, you should start the Rails server. If you like, you can create a [startup.sh](/docs/boxes/startup/) file to start whenever your project loads. 1. **Preview** : This previews your app in a new browser window. ## Accessing the application To access your application from a browser, you can use the menu option described above. The url of your Rails project can be found in the `Project->Box Info` menu and will look something like this ``` http://vital-ego.box.codio.io:3000/ ``` ## How the Pack was prepared This Starter Pack was built on the `Rails` Codio Certified Stack (Node, Grunt, MongoDB, Rails). The following commands were used to create the code workspace ```bash gem install rails rails new . ``` ## Useful Links - [Ruby on Rails documentation](h",J,Information and communication,high,"The repository is a basic Ruby on Rails application, which is commonly used for web development and software applications. This aligns with the Information and communication industry, as it involves the creation and deployment of web-based applications."
384698172,react-punto-de-venta,joelibaceta/react-punto-de-venta,,,JavaScript,"JavaScript, CSS, HTML",1,0,1,0,2021-07-10T12:57:44Z,2023-02-02T02:46:09Z,2021-07-10T12:58:27Z,,"# Getting Started with Create React App This project was bootstrapped with [Create React App](https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app). ## Available Scripts In the project directory, you can run: ### `yarn start` Runs the app in the development mode.\ Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to view it in the browser. The page will reload if you make edits.\ You will also see any lint errors in the console. ### `yarn test` Launches the test runner in the interactive watch mode.\ See the section about [running tests](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/running-tests) for more information. ### `yarn build` Builds the app for production to the `build` folder.\ It correctly bundles React in production mode and optimizes the build for the best performance. The build is minified and the filenames include the hashes.\ Your app is ready to be deployed! See the section about [deployment](https://facebook.github.io/create-react-app/docs/deployment) for more informati",G,Wholesale and retail trade,high,"The repository name 'react-punto-de-venta' suggests it is related to point-of-sale systems, which are commonly used in the retail industry for sales transactions."
992086150,resilient-turnstile,joelibaceta/resilient-turnstile,Estación SatNOGS en Lima con monitoreo estructural activo (Proyecto Replicable),"antenna, arduino, noaa, raspbery-pi, satellite, satnogs, turnstile",C++,"C++, Python, JavaScript, Shell, HTML, C, CSS",2,0,2,0,2025-05-28T15:40:34Z,2025-07-04T21:19:37Z,2025-06-08T11:51:36Z,,"# Resilient Turnstile – Estación SatNOGS con Monitoreo Autónomo Este repositorio tiene como finalidad proporcionar una implementación reproducible y documentada de una estación SatNOGS con capacidades de monitoreo estructural activo, basada en sensores embebidos. Se incluyen diagramas de conexión, archivos STL para componentes impresos en 3D, el código fuente modular para microcontroladores, scripts de integración con Raspberry Pi, así como evidencia del despliegue exitoso. [![Imagen de la estación SatNOGS](figs/StationPage.png)](https://network.satnogs.org/stations/4121) <p align=""center""> <img src=""figs/AntennaMonitor.png"" width=""50%""> </p> 📺 **[Ver video de funcionamiento](https://youtu.be/yltyIin1x2w)** --- El caso de estudio corresponde a la estación instalada en Lima, Perú (Nodo 4121), equipada con una antena turnstile construida artesanalmente y un sistema de monitoreo capaz de detectar impactos, caídas y sobrecalentamiento, generando eventos estructurados por puerto serial para",M,"Professional, scientific activities",high,"The repository focuses on the implementation of a satellite ground station with structural monitoring capabilities, which aligns with scientific research and professional activities in the field of satellite communications and environmental monitoring."
995031210,ResNet-18,joelibaceta/ResNet-18,"C++ implementation of ResNet-18 for image classification. Inference-ready, modular, and compatible with PyTorch-exported weights.",,,,0,0,0,0,2025-06-02T21:28:59Z,2025-09-15T09:55:08Z,2025-06-02T22:30:41Z,,"# 🧠 ResNet-18 C++ Implementation This repository provides a faithful **C++ implementation** of the **ResNet-18 architecture**, adapted for **image classification tasks**. The model design follows the original *""Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition""* paper by He et al. (2015), and is intended for academic use and performance evaluation. Unlike typical Python-based deep learning workflows, this project focuses on performing **inference directly in C++** using pretrained weights exported from PyTorch. All core components — convolution, batch normalization, ReLU activation, residual connections, and fully connected layers — have been reimplemented in native C++. > 🔧 *Optional:* This project can be extended to support GPU acceleration on macOS via **Metal Performance Shaders (MPS)**. ## ✨ Features - ResNet-18 architecture implemented from scratch in C++ - Inference pipeline for real-world image data - Compatible with pretrained weights exported from PyTorch - Modular, extensible cod",M,"Professional, scientific activities",high,"The repository provides a C++ implementation of the ResNet-18 architecture for image classification, which is primarily used in research and academic settings, aligning it closely with professional and scientific activities."
1004467353,restaurant-microservices-demo,joelibaceta/restaurant-microservices-demo,Este repositorio contiene un proyecto educativo para demostrar una arquitectura simple de microservicios,,Python,"Python, Dockerfile, Shell",1,0,1,0,2025-06-18T17:04:42Z,2025-09-15T09:55:43Z,2025-06-19T04:06:36Z,,"# Microservicios de Restaurante con IAM y Service Discovery Este repositorio contiene un proyecto educativo para demostrar **una arquitectura moderna de microservicios**, integrando: - ✅ Múltiples microservicios (`order`, `kitchen`, `delivery`) - 🔐 Un sistema de autenticación (IAM) usando tokens - 🔎 **Service Discovery** con Consul - 🌐 API Gateway dinámico con `nginx` y `consul-template` - ⚙️ Escalabilidad, seguridad y resiliencia Ideal para enseñar los principios de **diseño de microservicios, descubrimiento de servicios, e integración de seguridad descentralizada**. --- ## 📊 Diagrama de arquitectura (Mermaid) ```mermaid graph LR subgraph Cliente A[Usuario con token JWT] end subgraph Gateway G[NGINX + consul-template] G --> |auth_request| IAM G --> Order G --> Kitchen G --> Delivery end subgraph Microservicios Order[Order Service] Kitchen[Kitchen Service] Delivery[Delivery Service] end subgraph Discovery Consul[Consul] end subgraph Autenticación IAM[Simple IAM Service] end A --> G Ord",I,Accommodation and food services,high,"The repository is focused on a microservices architecture for a restaurant application, which directly relates to the food services industry. It demonstrates components like order management, kitchen operations, and delivery services, making it highly relevant to accommodation and food services."
1048778046,restaurant-vision-demo,joelibaceta/restaurant-vision-demo,Detección y análisis de ocupación de mesas en restaurantes usando Computer Vision y Deep Learning.,"cctv, computer-vision, restaurant, yolo, yolov8",Python,"Python, Shell",0,0,0,0,2025-09-02T02:33:16Z,2025-09-03T17:42:34Z,2025-09-03T17:42:30Z,,"# 🍽️ Restaurant Vision Demo Detección y análisis de ocupación de mesas en restaurantes usando Computer Vision y Deep Learning. ## 📋 Descripción Este proyecto utiliza YOLO v8 para detectar personas en tiempo real y analizar la ocupación de mesas en un restaurante. El sistema puede procesar videos, detectar clientes sentados, clasificar personal (staff) vs clientes, y generar reportes de ocupación con visualización en tiempo real. ![screen](/figs/screenshot.png) ## ✨ Características - 🎯 **Detección de personas** con YOLO v8 y análisis de pose - 👥 **Tracking inteligente** de personas con tolerancia a oclusiones - 🏠 **Análisis de ocupación** de mesas por ROI (Region of Interest) - 👔 **Clasificación staff vs clientes** usando patrones de movimiento - 📊 **Panel de visualización** en tiempo real con estado de mesas - 📹 **Procesamiento de video** con salida grabada - 📈 **Exportación de datos** en formato CSV para análisis ## 🏗️ Arquitectura del Sistema ### Estrategia Modular El proyecto utiliz",I,Accommodation and food services,high,"The repository focuses on detecting and analyzing table occupancy in restaurants using computer vision and deep learning, which directly serves the accommodation and food services industry."
