282569266,wifi-tracing,joelibaceta/wifi-tracing,A contact tracing hackaton idea,,Java,"Java, HTML, JavaScript, Python, Dockerfile, CSS, Shell",17,0,17,5,2020-07-26T03:38:59Z,2023-03-13T01:52:23Z,2022-12-10T10:02:39Z,GNU General Public License v3.0,"![](doc/images/project_banner.svg) Inspired by [bluetrace](https://bluetrace.io/) <br /> This alternative propose to use a mutiple wifi signal strength measurements to guess positions within a physical location. Serve data with indoor x,y positions for contact tracing ![](doc/images/main_screenshot.png) This demo contains: - An android and raspberry aplications as end user applications. - A website to monitor the people position in a floorplan. (For demo purpose only) - A backend where historical positioning data is stored ## How it works? 1. Get the distances from the main wifi points. ![](doc/images/Sample.svg) Python ```python def scan(interface='wlan0'): cmd = [""iwlist"", interface, ""scan""] proc = subprocess.Popen(cmd, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE) points = proc.stdout.read().decode('utf-8') return points ``` Android ```java IntentFilter intentFilter = new IntentFilter(); intentFilter.addAction(WifiManager.SCAN_RESULTS_AVAILABLE_ACTION); registerReceiver(wifiScanRe",Q,Human health and social work,high,"The repository focuses on contact tracing, which is directly related to public health efforts, especially in managing and tracking the spread of diseases. This application serves the healthcare industry by utilizing technology to enhance contact tracing capabilities."
