164905274,DLcoursera,csaybar/DLcoursera,Coursera Deep Learning Specialization,,Jupyter Notebook,"Jupyter Notebook, Python",31,22,31,0,2019-01-09T17:11:38Z,2025-06-16T15:43:28Z,2019-06-07T09:57:38Z,,"# Deep Learning Specialization on Coursera **Master Deep Learning, and Break into AI** Instructor: [Andrew Ng](http://www.andrewng.org/) ## Introduction This repo contains all my programming assignments. I transcripted all the problems to google colab to being everything more reproducible. ## ¿What is colab? Google **colab** is a free cloud service (jupyter as service) with GPU and TPU support. <img class=""center"" height=""200"" src=""https://colab.research.google.com/img/colab_favicon_256px.png"" > ## Course 01: Neural Networks and Deep Learning ### Logistic Regression (Week02) <table align=""left""><td> <a target=""_blank"" href=""https://colab.research.google.com/github/csaybar/DLcoursera/blob/master/Neural%20Networks%20and%20Deep%20Learning/week2/Logistic%20Regression%20as%20a%20Neural%20Network/Logistic%2BRegression%2Bwith%2Ba%2BNeural%2BNetwork%2Bmindset%2Bv5.ipynb""> <img src=""https://www.tensorflow.org/images/colab_logo_32px.png"" />Run in Google Colab </a> </td><td> <a target=""_blank"" hr",P,Education,high,"The repository contains programming assignments related to a Deep Learning Specialization course on Coursera, indicating its primary purpose is educational."
