37621402,porter_duff_browser_android,emedinaa/porter_duff_browser_android,Demo of Porter-Duff Transfer Modes on Android,,Java,Java,0,0,0,0,2015-06-17T21:17:19Z,2023-09-24T02:56:59Z,2015-01-06T22:28:32Z,Apache License 2.0,"Porter-Duff Browser is a sample Android application that displays the effect of the various options available for an android.graphics.PorterDuffXfermode. The display shows the source and destination sample images (simple colour-alpha ramps), and underneath that a scrolling list of the effects of the different modes on those images. Contents: src/ -- Java sources for the Android app res/ -- resources for the Android app AndroidManifest.xml, build.xml, *.properties -- for driving Google's Android build tools (note that you will have to provide a couple more of these--see INSTALL for details) README -- this file INSTALL -- build/installation instructions LICENSE -- licence (Apache 2.0, same as Google's sample code) A prebuilt binary is available in the Google Play store here <https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=nz.gen.geek_central.porter_duff_browser>. Lawrence D'Oliveiro <ldo@geek-central.gen.nz>",J,Information and communication,high,"The repository is a demo application showcasing graphics rendering techniques in Android, which falls under software development and communication technologies."
